<\/span> in <span class=\"labels\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"labels\">British English<\/span>, especially in the north of the country and in schools:<ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">I make sure my kids have a hot school dinner, not just a packed lunch.<\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class=\"li\">A main meal eaten in the evening is usually called <span class=\"eb\">dinner<\/span>, especially if it is a formal meal. <span class=\"eb\">Supper<\/span> is also an evening meal, but more informal than <span class=\"eb\">dinner<\/span> and usually eaten at home. It can also be a late meal or something to eat and drink before going to bed.<\/li><li class=\"li\">In <span class=\"labels\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"labels\">British English<\/span>, <span class=\"eb\">tea<\/span> is a light meal in the afternoon with sandwiches, cakes, etc. and a cup of tea:<ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">a cream tea.<\/span><\/li><\/ul> It can also be a main meal eaten early in the evening, especially by children:<ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">What time do the kids have their tea?<\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class=\"li\">As a general rule, if <span class=\"eb\">dinner<\/span> is the word someone uses for the meal in the middle of the day, they probably call the meal in the evening <span class=\"eb\">tea<\/span> or <span class=\"eb\">supper<\/span>. If they call the meal in the middle of the day <span class=\"eb\">lunch<\/span>, they probably call the meal in the evening <span class=\"eb\">dinner<\/span>.<\/li><li class=\"li\"><span class=\"eb\">Brunch<\/span>, a combination of breakfast and lunch, is becoming more common, especially as a meal where your guests serve themselves.<\/li><\/ul><\/span><\/div><div class=\"coll\"><div class=\"box\"><span>Extra Examples<\/span><\/div><ul class=\"example